					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Yikes, it has been a hot minute since I've had a chance to post a tale on the wiki.</p> <p>This article was written for the 2020 Art Exchange for <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2527320&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609712313" alt="LordStonefish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2527320)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" >LordStonefish</a></span> who requested an installment for their <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/glittering-horizon-hub">Glittering Horizons</a> tale series.</p> <p>Having a chance to read Glittering Horizons, a tale series about</p> <blockquote> <p>a murder, the aftermath, the Photography Division, the Church of the Second Hytoth, alternate universes, the mysterious Director Van Turner, and much more.</p> </blockquote> <p>I hope you all find it a compelling addition to what is a very intriguing mystery so far.</p> <p>Anyway, enjoy the tale!</p> <p><em>JC</em></p> 
