				<title>A Story From a Future</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13968758/a-story-from-a-future</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 03 Jan 2021 19:50:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Doggol</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6991250</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A tale I've been thinking about for a while now.</p> <p><strong>Some Related Stuff</strong></p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Whats&nbsp;going&nbsp;on&nbsp;here</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">hide</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p><strong>Universe Designation:</strong> My conception of the foundation multiverse has the universes categorised by their differences. ξ denotes the average amount of humes in the universe, assuming it was a close system (which it turns, out, is not the case). So ξ-0.24 means it has 0.24% less reality than the baseline canon. This is what causes the crisis to begin so early (it happens in every universe, but this one is more susceptible).</p> <p>This universe is also uniquely susceptible to this event because of many things going wrong throughout its history (this will be expanded upon)</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
